{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"Graduate src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py (867 LOC, over the 800 soft cap) off the module-size allowlist by extracting the cryptographic-identity & signed-attestation fold cluster into a NEW pure, stdlib-free leaf src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py.\n\nMOVE (by name): _fold_author_attribution, _rederive_keyring_keys, process_key_event, _bootstrap_genesis_keyring, attestation_kind, process_signature. These reference only each other (a true leaf): process_key_event calls _rederive_keyring_keys; process_signature calls attestation_kind and _fold_author_attribution. _processors.py imports them back and re-exports them (# noqa: F401) so rebar.reducer._processors.<symbol> keeps resolving for the reducer dispatch table (_replay.py imports process_key_event + process_signature from ._processors) and for attestation_kind's importers (signing.py, _commands/verify_opcert.py, _opcert_signing.py, and tests). reducer/__init__.py needs no change.\n\nDEVIATION from the docs/architecture.md offenders row: that row names the seam _processors_keys.py with ONLY the 4-function keys cluster and explicitly flags it SUB-FLOOR (~84 LOC, below the 100-LOC leaf floor). This ticket WIDENS the seam to also move the attestation pair (attestation_kind + process_signature) so the new leaf clears the 100-LOC floor, and names it _processors_identity.py. _fold_author_attribution MUST travel with process_signature (its caller) into the leaf, else a back-edge cycle forms. The sub-floor _processors_keys.py row is stale/superseded and is DELETED by this ticket.\n\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor: no signature or logic changes; E5 testing-plan is not-applicable — the existing reducer/attestation/signing test suites are the oracle.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] New leaf src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py is in [100,800] LOC. Verified by: `wc -l src/rebar/reducer/_processors_identity.py`.\n- [ ] src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py is <=800 LOC (down from 867). Verified by: `wc -l src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py`.\n- [ ] The 6 named symbols live in the leaf and are re-exported (# noqa: F401) from _processors.py so back-compat holds. Verified by: `python -c \"from rebar.reducer._processors import process_key_event, process_signature, attestation_kind, _fold_author_attribution, _rederive_keyring_keys, _bootstrap_genesis_keyring; print('ok')\"`.\n- [ ] _processors.py removed from .github/module-size-allowlist.txt and .github/module-size-ceilings.txt. Verified by: `! grep -q '_processors.py' .github/module-size-allowlist.txt && ! grep -q 'reducer/_processors.py ' .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`.\n- [ ] The stale offenders-table row is deleted from docs/architecture.md. Verified by: `! grep -q _processors_keys docs/architecture.md`.\n- [ ] make lint passes (ruff check + ruff format --check). Verified by: `make lint`.\n- [ ] tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py passes (allowlist == over-cap set == ceilings keys). Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`.\n- [ ] The reducer/attestation/signing suites pass. Verified by: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_attestations_reducer.py tests/unit/test_signing.py tests/unit/test_legacy_signature_mirror_drop.py -q` and `python -m pytest tests/unit -k 'reducer or attestation or signing' -q`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784398008941159001,"uuid":"7ce7330e-d56c-456b-aea6-64ab4eea4303"}